---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ProjectCard from '../components/ProjectCard.astro';
import { getEntry } from 'astro:content';

const copilot = await getEntry('projects', 'mortgage-readiness-copilot');
---
<BaseLayout pageTitle="About — Jiri Sindelar" description="About Jiri Sindelar — software engineer, builder, learner.">

  <section class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-6 sm:gap-8 items-start">
    <img
      src="/jirka-photo.png"
      alt="Jiri Sindelar"
      class="w-48 h-48 sm:w-56 sm:h-56 rounded-xl object-cover shrink-0"
    />
    <div>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold">Jiri Sindelar</h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-lg text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
        Deep in flow, exploring new ideas emerging in software.
        Lately, I’ve been digging into Open Banking and building an agentic app.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-4 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">The story</h2>
    <p>
      Coming in the office, checking JIRA, standup, coding, consulting, planning... peaceful ordinary day in ordinary developer's life, 
      full of jokes and smile with my dear colleagues. But something was brewing.
      </p>
      <p>
      I had great years in Prague's banking - working on Java backends, 
      surrounded by brilliant people who'd built software around the world, understanding the whole business around.
      I admired them uncritically and learned a lot from them. But in my thoughts it was like: 
      "Hmm.. being able to invent things to people in every corner of the world who would never have imagined that such a thing could exist. 
      It's so cool... damn!" 
      I recalled a story of my grandpa about his first day at work:
      Shop foreman: <em class="text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400">"Who are you?</em>, 
      Grandpa: <em class="text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400">a panel beater</em>, 
      Shop foreman: <em class="text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400">Maybe one day. For now, you're steam off a panel beater's shit."</em>
      This old hand got experienced welding aluminium wings for Messerschmitts or repairing cars in the campaign of Stalingrad.
      Take your time to realize what challenges (and disasters) those men experienced there. 
      The unexpected association there between my colleagues and colleague of my grandpa is
      that both possessed the full breadth of knowledge. He wasn't just able to build or repair everything 
      but had got a wisdom, knowledge of the world. And I felt like the apprentice.
    </p>
    <p>
      Back to computers. "Oh yeah, experience abroad. But how to do that? 
      Where? How? What? For who?"
      Well, I brained, googled, chatgpted... hard and finally I picked Melbourne, Australia. 
      A lot of people, companies, they need solutions. 
      And also tech scene, fresh ideas, so I can learn from them, collaborate, be part of it. 
      The city is liveable, English speaking, and I can get a working visa. Yeah, that's why I am in Melbourne. 
      And finally I got to try inventing something potentially useful in fintech domain which I am already familiar with. 
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-4 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">What I'm into now</h2>
    <p>
      Here's what I'm exploring right now — came out of an idea that mortgage 
      assessment is still user unfriendly, if you have multiple accounts it's time-spending and annoying activity, 
      the Open Banking gives the access to client's financial data and AI agents can make it easier:
    </p>
    {copilot && (
      <ProjectCard
        slug={copilot.id}
        title={copilot.data.title}
        description={copilot.data.description}
        tags={copilot.data.tags}
        sourceUrl={copilot.data.sourceUrl}
        liveUrl={copilot.data.liveUrl}
      />
    )}
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-4 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">What I'm open to</h2>
    <p>
      If you're into Open Banking, agentic design, or product development, let's chat!
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-4 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Outside of code</h2>
    <p>
      Improv, history, philosophy, volunteering, and nature.
    </p>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
